cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper is about computer vision and machine learning techniques for object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses Linear Discriminant Analysis (LDA) and correlation filters, which are machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of structured covariance matrices, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the time and memory efficiency of the proposed method, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
